The six men accused of murdering Babita Deokaran were denied bail in the Johannesburg Magistrate's Court. JOHANNESBURG - Six men accused of murdering whistleblower, Babita Deokaran are expected to return to the Johannesburg Magistrate's Court on Tuesday. They appeared briefly in court in February before the matter was postponed. Deokaran was gunned down outside her Winchester Hills home in Johannesburg in August. READ:Â Babita Deokaran murder suspects back in court She was to be a key witness in a case involving dodgy PPE contracts at the Gauteng Health Department where she was a senior official. The State does not want the accused released on bail. It believes their safety will be compromised as the mastermind behind Deokaran's murder is yet to be uncovered.